{"title":"Velo Orange’s Yakimono Bike Project","link":"https://theradavist.com/velo-orange-yakimono-bike-project/","date":1730906658000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_03.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_03.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/shanesellers1/?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">Shane Sellers</a> is an artist, educator, Philly Bike Expo ambassador and Velo Orange collaborator. <span>Their recent project converted a <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/velo-oranges-neutrino-a-minivelo-with-big-capabilities/\" target=\"_blank\">Neutrino</a> into a “Yakimono Bike,” where they open air-fired grips and a saddle using traditional Japanese methods.</span> The mini velo was then outfitted with a display case, where Shane displayed traditional Yakimono pottery.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_02.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_02.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/11/Yakimono_Bike_02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Check out the full project on the <a href=\"https://velo-orange.com/blogs/theveloorangeblog/intersection-yakimono-bike\" target=\"_blank\">Velo Orange blog</a>!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/velo-orange-yakimono-bike-project/\">Velo Orange’s Yakimono Bike Project</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"117b3a10ee321476dfcabca4d16cd179e2058ceeba58e10c69290c0265a7c93f","category":"Cycling"}